<h1>MAT1260 Formula Sheet</h1>

<h2>Descriptive Statistics</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Relative frequency: frequency / (sum of all frequencies)</li>
  <li>Class midpoint: \((\text{lower class limit}_i + \text{lower class limit}_{i+1}) / 2\)</li>
  <li>Mean: \(\bar{x} = \frac{\sum x_i}{n}\)</li>
  <li>Population standard deviation: \(\sigma = \sqrt{\frac{\sum (x_i - \mu)^2}{N}}\)</li>
  <li>Sample standard deviation: \(s = \sqrt{\frac{\sum (x_i - \bar{x})^2}{n-1}}\)</li>
  <li>Population variance: \(\sigma^2 = \text{Var.P(numbers)}\)</li>
  <li>Sample variance: \(s^2 = \text{Var.S(numbers)}\)</li>
</ul>

<h2>Z-scores and Quartiles</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Z-score: \(z = \frac{x - \mu}{\sigma}\)</li>
  <li>Find x from z: \(x = \mu + z\sigma\)</li>
  <li>Quartiles: \(Q_1 = \text{QUARTILE.INC(numbers,1)}, Q_2 = \text{QUARTILE.INC(numbers,2)}, Q_3 = \text{QUARTILE.INC(numbers,3)}\)</li>
  <li>IQR: \(\text{IQR} = Q_3 - Q_1\)</li>
  <li>Fences: \(\text{Lower fence} = Q_1 - 1.5 \cdot \text{IQR}, \text{Upper fence} = Q_3 + 1.5 \cdot \text{IQR}\)</li>
  <li>Five-number summary: Min, Q1, Q2, Q3, Max</li>
</ul>

<h2>Correlation and Regression</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Correlation coefficient: \(r = \text{CORREL(array1, array2)}\)</li>
  <li>Regression line: \(y = mx + b\)</li>
  <li>Slope: \(m = \text{SLOPE(ys,xs)}\)</li>
  <li>Intercept: \(b = \text{INTERCEPT(ys,xs)}\)</li>
  <li>Residual: \(\text{Residual} = \text{Observed value} - \text{Predicted value}\)</li>
</ul>

<h2>Probability Rules</h2>
<ul>
  <li>General Addition Rule: \(P(A \text{ or } B) = P(A) + P(B) - P(A \text{ and } B)\)</li>
  <li>Complement Rule: \(P(A^c) = 1 - P(A)\)</li>
  <li>Multiplication Rule: \(P(A \text{ and } B) = P(A) \cdot P(B|A)\)</li>
  <li>Conditional Probability: \(P(A|B) = \frac{P(A \text{ and } B)}{P(B)}\)</li>
</ul>

<h2>Binomial Distribution</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Mean: \(\mu_{bi} = n \cdot p\)</li>
  <li>Standard deviation: \(\sigma_{bi} = \sqrt{n \cdot p \cdot (1-p)}\)</li>
  <li>Excel: <code>BINOM.DIST(x, trials, probability, FALSE)</code></li>
</ul>

<h2>Normal Distribution</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Area to the left: \(P(X \le x) = \text{NORM.DIST}(x, \text{mean}, \text{sd}, \text{TRUE})\)</li>
  <li>Area to the right: \(P(X > x) = 1 - \text{NORM.DIST}(x, \text{mean}, \text{sd}, \text{TRUE})\)</li>
  <li>Area between: \(P(a \le X \le b) = \text{NORM.DIST}(b, \text{mean}, \text{sd}, \text{TRUE}) - \text{NORM.DIST}(a, \text{mean}, \text{sd}, \text{TRUE})\)</li>
  <li>Given percentile, find number: \(x = \text{NORM.INV}(\text{area}, \text{mean}, \text{sd})\)</li>
</ul>

<h2>Sampling Distributions</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Sample mean: \(\mu_{\bar{x}} = \mu\)</li>
  <li>Std dev of sample mean: \(\sigma_{\bar{x}} = \frac{\sigma}{\sqrt{n}}\)</li>
  <li>Sample proportion: \(\hat{p} = \frac{x}{n}\)</li>
  <li>Mean of sample proportion: \(\mu_{\hat{p}} = p\)</li>
  <li>Std dev of sample proportion: \(\sigma_{\hat{p}} = \sqrt{\frac{p(1-p)}{n}}\)</li>
</ul>

